               <head>Munajat</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Munājāt by Anṣārī al-Harawī, ʻAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad, 1006-1089</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104964 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/nr96038220" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15597-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_19703891">Anṣārī al-Harawī, ʻAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad, 1006-1089</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ara" key="person_19703891" type="supplied">انصارى الهروى، عبد الله بن محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20399">Munājāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20399">مناجات</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>The Munājāt, or intimate discourses with God, also known by the title <title>Ilahī-nāmah</title>, wholly or partly by Khwājah ‘Abd Allāh Anṣārī Haravī (396-481/1006-1088). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The present manuscript is an outstanding calligraphic copied by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_39279060" role="scr">Mīr ‘Imād al-Ḥasanī</persName>. Dated <name type="place">Tabriz</name> (bi-Dār al-salṭanat Tabrīz), 990/1582.
                        </p>
                        <p>Other contents: 1r, ownership inscriptions, one describing the work as Maqālāt-i Khvājah ‘Abd Allāh Anṣārī on 8 folios, and one dated 1272/1855-6; and seal impressions. 1v, fainter seal impressions. </p>
                        <p>Title supplied. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation />
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
